summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 11288, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Third Avenue, in the City of Seattle, from Union Street to Yesler Way, by grading the same to the grade established by Ordinance No. 11276, of said of City of Seattle, and by regrading the streets crossing said Third Avenue, between said Union Street and Yesler Way, and providing for the payment of the cost and expense of said improvement by the issuing and sale of bonds, in the manned provided by the laws of the State of Washington, and Ordinance No. 5693 and the Charter of the City of Seattle.
